                "s2_paper_id": "044d9850bdf23c72cb1adcdd20d5d3c9f473bf0f",
                "title": "Reciprocity for GL(2) L-functions twisted by Dirichlet characters",
                "year": 2025,
                "venue": "",
                "citation_count": 0,
                "reference_count": 10,
                "abstract": "A formula connecting a moment of L-functions and a dual moment in a way that interchanges the roles of certain key parameters on both sides is known as a reciprocity relation. We establish a reciprocity relation for a first moment of GL(2) L-functions twisted by Dirichlet characters. This extends, via a new and simple argument, some results of Bettin, Drappeau, and Nordentoft.",
