            {
                "s2_paper_id": "9e651df01fb80bc9967d1f2c51b36813255a3bb7",
                "title": "Upper Bounds for Analytic Ranks of Elliptic Curves Over Cyclotomic Fields",
                "year": 2025,
                "venue": "International mathematics research notices",
                "citation_count": 0,
                "reference_count": 11,
                "abstract": "\n Let $E$ be an elliptic curve defined over $\\mathbb Q$. We show that the analytic rank of $E$ over the cyclotomic extension $\\mathbb{Q}(e^{2\\pi i/q})$ is bounded above by $q^{45/52+\\varepsilon }$, as $q\\to \\infty $ through the primes. This improves the bound $q^{7/8+\\varepsilon }$ established by Chinta.",
